00:00:20.450 --> 00:00:21.445
position vectors.

00:00:21.445 --> 00:00:23.390
So this is R2 right here.

00:00:23.390 --> 00:00:26.990
So my first position vector
is the zero vector.

00:00:26.990 --> 00:00:31.050
So it just specifies the point
right there, so it's 0, 0.

00:00:31.050 --> 00:00:40.720
My second point is specified the
by the vector say k 1, 0,

00:00:40.720 --> 00:00:42.720
so some constant times 0.

00:00:42.720 --> 00:00:44.210
Let me write it a little
bit neater than that,

00:00:44.210 --> 00:00:46.020
a little bit bigger.

00:00:46.020 --> 00:00:50.960
So it's k 1, 0, so that's my
second position vector, which

00:00:50.960 --> 00:00:53.220
would specify that point
