a determinant.

00:19:55.850 --> 00:19:58.100
A determinant of a
transformation matrix is

00:19:58.100 --> 00:20:02.190
essentially a scaling factor for
area as you map from one

00:20:02.190 --> 00:20:05.560
region to another region, or
as we go from one region to

00:20:05.560 --> 00:20:08.590
the image of that region under
